   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Multi-Feature Random Forest Classification Model: Pokémon Attribute Analysis\n",
    "### Created By - Daniel Therattil"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b16b1eaa-0f7f-44e8-b5ea-62b188c849aa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Introduction"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f11a86f9-b475-4361-98f4-2eae2bf559f0",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I made this project to uncover underlying patterns that differentiate 'Special' Pokémon from their normal counterparts across all nine generations of data. These 'Special' Pokémon include 'Legendaries', 'Sub-legendaries', and 'Mythic' Pokémon. By utilizing a Random Forest Classification model and performing Feature Importance analysis, I identified which specific attributes such as attack, speed, or physical height serve as the crucial indicators of a Pokémon's status. My final model achieved a 95% test accuracy, proving that 'Special' Pokémon follow a distinct set of numerical rules that separate them from their normal counterparts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "218f8cf7-23e0-4f05-96ec-9397a88a5765",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Data Preparation & Cleaning"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dd76f24f-749b-4db0-89b3-854ead66d95c",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "This section covers the initial preparation of the Gen 1–9 Pokémon dataset required for the machine learning model. Key steps included handling missing physical stats and merging all non-normal categories in the 'status' column into a single 'Special' target variable for the Random Forest model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f0b42f97-16ca-4221-a1b9-806f0fdfff1e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Importing Libraries"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "2324fa27-5265-4e70-b171-c9dbd118d52d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import pandas as pd\n",
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import seaborn as sns\n",
    "from sklearn.tree import DecisionTreeClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.ensemble import RandomForestClassifier\n",
    "from sklearn.metrics import accuracy_score\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import train_test_split\n",
    "from sklearn.model_selection import cross_val_score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6bd81db0-e50c-4562-ad1e-f1a5a4893941",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Data Preparation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "8aeb9f08-2e62-4f50-8893-f0b544eac4dd",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To prepare the data we begin by creating the dataframe and inspecting it for missing values before consolidating the target variable for our model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "87ae3ea8-9037-45e6-a0e0-30f975aeec2a",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df = pd.read_csv("pokemon.csv") #Creating dataframe of the dataset \"pokemon.csv\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "9998047c-1418-44ff-ad90-638313fe5611",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
