     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "print(\"Missing values\")\n",
    "print(df.isnull().sum())"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0bf624b4-9d2d-44b3-b350-3e5f2fad8b06",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Due to a high volume of missing values in features such as \"base_friendship\", \"base_experience\", \"percentage_male\", these columns will be omitted. Removing these limited features ensures better data integrity and prevents the model from learning from incomplete or biased noise."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "2e6cb8f0-f195-466e-8738-af47cc2edaaa",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Target Engineering"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "d87fd7a7-7a95-4f63-93d2-b3334e8b595e",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I inspected the status column to identify which categories should be included into the 'Special' target variable. This allows the model to focus on the broad characteristics that distinguish Pokémon in the 'Special' category as opposed to 'normal' status Pokémon. "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "12dce7dc-86d3-4e2e-ab44-eac4348554c9",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array(['Normal', 'Sub Legendary', 'Legendary', 'Mythical'], dtype=object)"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 4,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "df['status'].unique() #Lists out every possible type of variable in the column \"status\"."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "be84aaa6-aa41-40c8-ab16-de976a7af769",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "df['special'] = df['status'].isin(['Sub Legendary', 'Legendary', 'Mythical']).astype(int) #Created a new column in dataframe of all Pokémon with a status besides normal."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f955b061-d1c2-417d-9b4d-731419ee9003",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Exploratory Data Analysis"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0bd9f57e-f46d-40ea-a234-91a56fdfd50b",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "With the data cleaned and the target variable defined, I chose to conduct an Exploratory Data Analysis. By visualizing the distribution of battle stats, I could verify the 'power gap' between the two groups and ensure that the features selected for the Random Forest showed clear, predictive patterns.\""
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0443cb83-219b-435d-bb60-43e156af08d5",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Boxplot Analysis: Stat Power Gaps"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 6,
   "id": "08b82975-3055-4a35-a8e1-77ecc8361f12",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 800x400 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize=(8, 4))\n",
    "sns.boxplot(x ='special', y = 'sp_attack', data = df)\n",
    "plt.title('Special Attack Stat Comparison')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Status (0 = Normal, 1 = Special)')\n",
    "plt.ylabel('Special Attack Stats')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "fa2b4359-45b9-459b-bfea-4b1d30f42136",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    " As shown above, there is a clear stat difference between Pokémon in the 'Normal' and 'Special' status category. The median special attack for 'Special' Pokémon (approx. 110) is nearly double that of the Normal population (approx. 60). Furthermore, their interquartile ranges do not overlap, as evident by the blue boxes not being in same range of values, which in turn suggests that the special attack stat is significant differentiator between the 2 groups."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0a062fca-e9e4-44f2-adb0-e7fb84db2fbc",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Correlation Heatmap"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 7,
   "id": "26903a65-8c25-4496-9b93-052d84245786",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 1200x600 with 2 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "features = ['height_m','weight_kg','hp','attack','defense','sp_attack','sp_defense','speed', 'special']\n",
    "\n",
    "correlation_matrix = df[features].corr()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(12, 6))\n",
    "sns.heatmap(correlation_matrix, annot = True, cmap = 'vlag') #Chose colormap as vlag for clarity and annot to display actual correlation coefficient values.\n",
    "plt.title(\"Categories vs. 'Special' Status\")\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "6c35ca3a-877f-4d30-8a9a-c32efe5dee68",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The correlation heatmap clearly shows the 'Special' status can be correlated postively the most with weight_kg and sp_attack. Furthermore, height_m and weight_kg are heavily correlated with eachother indicating that as a Pokémon's height increases, its weight almost always increases. This could signify that 'Special' Pokémon are taller on average as well, since weight_kg is correlated positively with both height and special status. Overall, 'Special' Pokémon seem to have significant special attack stats and larger bodies as opposed to their normal counterparts."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "15076758-31d0-4714-ba53-39db23ac019f",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Model Development:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7690b054-c1f8-4013-b180-89d036ebc28d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Defining independent and target variables for the model:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "53b27733-ee37-4ffc-94b7-2850f7cffdce",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I selected the following columns as predictors based on their strong correlation with the target and their tested contribution to the accuracy of the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 8,
   "id": "4d42b3be-22ad-414c-bb40-8e0a1b0b7c21",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X = df[['height_m','weight_kg','hp','attack','defense','sp_attack','sp_defense','speed']] #Predictors\n",
    "Y =(df['special']) #Target for the model."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "010799c2-e0f4-4ec6-9acd-bbc91788cd9a",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Splitting the Data:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "67fc4b94-4e52-47d9-95c3-e20f6e1c2125",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "I utilized a Random Forest Classifier to predict the 'Special' status of Pokémon based on their combat and physical attributes. To ensure the model was free from overfitting, I performed an 80/20 train-test split and configured specific hyperparameters to prevent the trees from simply memorizing the training data. Furthermore, I found tweaking the depth of each tree to 4 helped with increasing the accuracy of the model greatly."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 9,
   "id": "a55784a6-e471-4e2e-906e-c596c9b50305",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "X_train, X_test, Y_train, Y_test = train_test_split(X,Y, test_size = 0.2, random_state = 1)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 10,
   "id": "56fa93ae-1bd7-439b-95c3-75b01357e07f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "forest = RandomForestClassifier(n_estimators = 150, max_depth = 4, random_state = 1).fit(X_train, Y_train)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 11,
   "id": "7dd9aa29-e99b-4a67-8ccd-e826465d6c8f",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.9501216545012166"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 11,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "accuracy_score(Y_train, forest.predict(X_train))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 12,
   "id": "570bf35d-d0ea-4803-8339-a2fb0039f851",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "0.9514563106796117"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 12,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "accuracy_score(Y_test, forest.predict(X_test))"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "06f38fbe-2ddd-457b-b776-3fba1b5e43ee",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "<u>Model accuracy:</u>\n",
    "<br>Training: 95% \n",
    "<br>Testing: 95.1%"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "1ad0ab60-6a34-425a-8886-182d20f50994",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "The accuracy performance across both datasets matching closely while still reaching a great accuracy confirms that the model has been generalized successfully in the train-test split."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "da572131-4d51-4d86-90e6-11d3001aa081",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Model Evaluation"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "dfa52875-d48c-4a38-8c32-b1f52ec83d83",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Cross evaluation "
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "0b6a0089-90ee-415b-be18-90583e8398ec",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "To ensure the model's high accuracy wasn't the result of a lucky random split I performed a cross valdiation to check whether the model's accuracy works amongst other splits. It helps determine whether or not the model was lucky for one batch. This process shuffles the data and validates the model multiple times, providing a more reliable estimate of how the model will perform on entirely new datasets."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 13,
   "id": "f4ed1fda-b1d9-4181-88d7-095591453838",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "text/plain": [
       "array([0.94174757, 0.9223301 , 0.94174757, 0.95145631, 0.89320388,\n",
       "       0.93203883, 0.93203883, 0.89320388, 0.91176471, 0.94117647])"
      ]
     },
     "execution_count": 13,
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "execute_result"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "score = cross_val_score(forest, X, Y, cv = 10)\n",
    "score"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 14,
   "id": "4d95dcbf-7170-4bc9-9790-06599ff3e6db",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "name": "stdout",
     "output_type": "stream",
     "text": [
      "The average accuracy amongst splits is  92.61%\n"
     ]
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "mean = score.mean()\n",
    "\n",
    "print(f\"The average accuracy amongst splits is {mean: .2%}\")"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "855c0f7b-00ad-4a1e-8949-170c020fd828",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Due to the overall accuracy remaining around 92% across various splits, we can say the model tends to be overall fairly accurate and reliable."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "23fb7cbb-bad7-40f4-a867-1c7c54644728",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "## Top Predictors/Feature Importance of Special Pokémon Status:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 15,
   "id": "6fc54379-963f-45e4-a7ec-05631d682572",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "importances = forest.feature_importances_\n",
    "model_importances = pd.Series(importances, index = X_train.columns)\n",
    "sorted_model_importances = model_importances.sort_values(ascending=True) #Just to make the plot more cohesive and easier to show prediction importance."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b46363ce-7e53-437b-b44b-05d9b2ddb5bb",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "### Plot importances:"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 16,
   "id": "1efa1890-6e3e-413a-8a11-b3c9c11a6755",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 900x500 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {},
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "plt.figure(figsize = (9,5))\n",
    "sorted_model_importances.plot(kind = 'barh', color='lightgreen')\n",
    "plt.title('What are the most important predictors for Pokémon that are not normal?')\n",
    "plt.xlabel('Importance Scores (Total = 1.0)')\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "a327ad15-4d90-4fe4-970a-7cc4e3ebcb4d",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Based on this graph we can see the feature importance analysis relied on predictors \"sp_attack\", \"speed\", and \"height_m\" to make its predictions on whether a Pokémon is not normal.\n"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "b971862a-92c1-4f44-b54a-99690f1baeef",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "# Conclusion"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "f7b13778-bef0-42f9-a558-753a37487d39",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Through this project, I successfully developed a Random Forest Classifier to predict the \"Special\" status of Pokémon based on their combat and physical attributes. The model I built achieved a robust 95.1% accuracy on unseen testing data. Furthermore, using cross validation yielded a mean accuracy of 92.61%, confirming that the model is highly reliable and generalizes well across the entire dataset not just one specific split. Moreover, the feature importance analysis revealed that predictors Special Attack, Speed, and Height are the primary predictors used by the model. This aligns with my early EDA findings, suggesting that \"Special\" Pokémon occupy a distinct niche characterized by greater offensive capabilities and larger physical proportions. All in all, the results demonstrate that a Pokémon bearing the \"Special\" status can be predicted by assessing a few key attributes such as \"sp_attack\", \"speed\", and \"height_m\"."
   ]
  }
